{
  "texts": [
    "If the data was not normally distributed, we used the Wilcoxon signed-ranks test instead of the paired t-test.",
    "Seventeen participants (94.4%) reported having sufficient experience with both types of support, so we included them in RQ3.",
    "One participant was excluded from the analysis due to a self-reported lack of experience with supports, leading to uncertainty in preference.",
    "To further unpack how CodeTailor contributed to the quantitative results, we investigated learners' think-aloud recordings and interviews.",
    "This allowed us to gain a better understanding of students' interactions with the programming support during practice."
  ]
}